<sn><md>###  **Bash Commands for File and Folder Operations**
---

| Command                | Description                                     | Example Usage                                 |                |
| ---------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- | -------------- |
| `ls`                   | List directory contents                         | `ls -l /home/user`                            |                |
| `cd`                   | Change directory                                | `cd Documents`                                |                |
| `pwd`                  | Print current working directory                 | `pwd`                                         |                |
| `mkdir`                | Create a new directory                          | `mkdir new_folder`                            |                |
| `rmdir`                | Remove an empty directory                       | `rmdir old_folder`                            |                |
| `rm`                   | Delete files or directories                     | `rm file.txt`, `rm -r folder/`                |                |
| `cp`                   | Copy files and directories                      | `cp file1.txt file2.txt`, `cp -r dir1/ dir2/` |                |
| `mv`                   | Move/rename files or directories                | `mv file.txt new_dir/`, `mv old new`          |                |
| `touch`                | Create a new empty file                         | `touch newfile.txt`                           |                |
| `cat`                  | Display file content                            | `cat file.txt`                                |                |
| `more` / `less`        | View large files page-by-page                   | `less bigfile.txt`                            |                |
| `head`                 | View the first lines of a file                  | `head -n 10 file.txt`                         |                |
| `tail`                 | View the last lines of a file                   | `tail -n 10 file.txt`                         |                |
| `find`                 | Search files/directories by name/type/size/etc. | `find . -name "*.txt"`                        |                |
| `locate`               | Quickly find files using system index           | `locate filename.txt`                         |                |
| `stat`                 | Display file or directory metadata              | `stat file.txt`                               |                |
| `file`                 | Identify file type                              | `file image.png`                              |                |
| `basename`             | Get the file name from a path                   | `basename /home/user/file.txt`                |                |
| `dirname`              | Get the directory path of a file                | `dirname /home/user/file.txt`                 |                |
| `du`                   | Estimate file/directory disk usage              | `du -sh folder/`                              |                |
| `df`                   | Show disk space usage                           | `df -h`                                       |                |
| `chmod`                | Change file permissions                         | `chmod 755 script.sh`                         |                |
| `chown`                | Change file owner and group                     | `chown user:group file.txt`                   |                |
| `lsattr` / `chattr`    | View/change file attributes on ext file systems | `lsattr file`, `chattr +i file`               |                |
| `tee`                  | Read and write output to a file simultaneously  | \`echo "hello"                                | tee file.txt\` |
| `xargs`                | Execute commands using input from a file        | \`cat list.txt                                | xargs rm\`     |
| `basename` / `dirname` | Extract filename or directory from a path       | `basename /path/file.txt`                     |                |
| `mktemp`               | Create temporary files/directories              | `mktemp` or `mktemp -d`                       |                |

---

